Section 1:
1 L.D. 1517
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 STATE AND LOCAL GOVERNMENT
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1002, L.D. 1517, “An Act to Replace
10 Participation Thresholds with Approval Thresholds in Certain School, Municipal and
11 County Measures”
12 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 7 and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 7. 30-A MRSA §2105, sub-§4, as enacted by PL 1987, c. 737, Pt. A, §2 and
14 Pt. C, §106 and amended by PL 1989, c. 6 and c. 9, §2 and c. 104, Pt. C, §§8 and 10, is
15 further amended to read:
16 4. Effective date. If a majority more of the ballots votes cast on any question under
17 subsection 1 or 2 favor acceptance than oppose it, the new charter, charter revision, charter
18 modification or charter amendment proposed in that question becomes effective as
19 provided in this subsection, provided as long as the total number of votes cast for and
20 against in favor of the question equals or exceeds 30% 15% of the total votes cast in the
21 municipality at the last gubernatorial election.
22 A. Except as provided in subparagraph (1), new charters, charter revisions or charter
23 modifications adopted by the voters take effect on the first day of the next succeeding
24 municipal year.
25 (1) New charters, charter revisions or charter modifications take effect
26 immediately for the purpose of conducting any elections required by the new
27 provisions.
28 B. Charter amendments adopted by the voters take effect on the date determined by
29 the municipal officers, but not later than the first day of the next municipal year.'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment, which is one of 2 reports of the committee, changes the requirements
3344 for a new municipal charter, charter revision, charter modification or charter amendment
Page 1 - 132LR1837(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1002, L.D. 1517
315 in a question before the voters to go into effect. Current law requires that the total number
326 of votes cast for and against the question equal or exceed 30% of the total votes cast in the
337 municipality in the last gubernatorial election. The amendment requires instead that the
348 number of votes cast in favor of the question exceed 15% of the total votes cast in the
359 municipality in the last gubernatorial election. Also, while the amendment does not change
460 the requirement that a majority of votes cast for and against the proposed change be in favor
471 of it in order for that change to go into effect, the amendment clarifies that blank votes are
482 not counted in that calculation.
Page 2 - 132LR1837(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
