13 'Sec. 7. 30-A MRSA §2105, sub-§4, as enacted by PL 1987, c. 737, Pt. A, §2 and
14 Pt. C, §106 and amended by PL 1989, c. 6 and c. 9, §2 and c. 104, Pt. C, §§8 and 10, is
15 further amended to read:
16 4. Effective date. If a majority more of the ballots votes cast on any question under
17 subsection 1 or 2 favor acceptance than oppose it, the new charter, charter revision, charter
18 modification or charter amendment proposed in that question becomes effective as
19 provided in this subsection, provided as long as the total number of votes cast for and
